<h1>Expense Reimbursement Policy</h1>
<p>In the course of your duties as an employee of [Business Name], you may be required to pay for goods/services that allow you to do your job. Any eligible expenses that you incur on behalf of Mirabilis will be reimbursed in full.</p>
<h3>Qualifying Expenses</h3>
<p>Mirabilis will reimburse all part and full-time employees for all qualifying expenses, including:</p>
<ul style="text-align: left;">
  <li>Travel for Business Purposes.</li>
  <li>Confrence Fees.</li>
  <li>Accommodations while attending meetings, conferences, etc.</li>
  <li>Office Supplies.</li>
  <li>Software required for work.</li>
  <li>Professional certification/membership fees.</li>
</ul>
<p>This list is by no means exhaustive. Employees should always get approval for reimbursement from their supervisors before incurring a work expense.</p>
<br>
<h3>Non-Qualifying Expenses</h3>
<p>There are certain expenses that Mirabilis will not be held responsible for, including:</p>
<ul style="text-align: left;">
  <li>Lost personal property.</li>
  <li>Unauthorized meals/entertainment.</li>
  <li>Fines incurred while operating a company vehicle</li>
  <li>Unauthorized flight upgrades, accommodations, etc.</li>
  <li>Expenses for spouses who accompany employees on business trips.</li>
  </ul>
  <h3>Procedure</h3>
  <p>In order to ensure that you are reimbursed for work-related expenses, follow these steps:</p>
  <ol style="text-align: left;">
    <li>Always keep receipts and submit them within 30 days.</li>
    <li>Affix all appliale receipts to the expense reimbursement form.</li>
    <li>Submit the form through the Expense Reimbursment Portal.</li>
  </ol>